Reasoning: The paper deals with the detection of fake images and videos using neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and few-shot learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper addresses the threat of Deepfake, which involves the manipulation of digital content, making it relevant to the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
